<emphasis box="[282,465,1493,1515]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Stirellus capitatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A, C: male pygofer and segment X–XI, lateral and dorsal view, respectively; B: male pygofer side, lateral view; D: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E–F: style, dorsal view; G: connective, dorsal view; H: aedeagus, dorsal view; I: connective and aedeagus, lateral view; J: aedeagus, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1621,2006]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1621,1646]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Body.</emphasis>
Vertex longer than twice width between eyes, elongately subtriangular, narrowed to apex which is broadly subacute (
<figureCitation box="[363,443,1657,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,1001,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[219,1367,990,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stirellus capitatus. Male. A – D: habitus, dorsal view; E: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255855/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
A–D, 5A–D). Ocellus far away from eye on anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1163,1233,1657,1682]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[241,1342,471,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[229,1358,454,1959]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Stirellus capitatus. Female. A – D: habitus, dorsal view; E: habitus, lateral view; F: face; G: the end of female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255856/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
E). Eye relatively small (
<figureCitation box="[228,306,1693,1718]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,1001,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[219,1367,990,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stirellus capitatus. Male. A – D: habitus, dorsal view; E: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255855/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
A–D, 5A–D). Anteclypeus tapering to apex, not extending beyond normal curve of genae (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1413,1693,1718]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,1001,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[219,1367,990,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stirellus capitatus. Male. A – D: habitus, dorsal view; E: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255855/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
E, 5F). Pronotum nearly as long as 0.5x median length of crown. Mesonotum and scutellum shorter than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[159,239,1765,1790]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,1001,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[219,1367,990,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stirellus capitatus. Male. A – D: habitus, dorsal view; E: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255855/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
A–D, 5A–D). Forewing macropterous to submacropterous, usually exposing apex of abdomen in female and sometimes in male (
<figureCitation box="[423,501,1801,1826]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,1001,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[219,1367,990,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Stirellus capitatus. Male. A – D: habitus, dorsal view; E: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255855/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
A–D, 5A–E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1621,2006]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1837,1862]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Male.</emphasis>
Pygofer side with few macrosetae dorsally, apex angulate (
<figureCitation box="[928,994,1837,1862]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,207,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[206,1381,193,1472]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Stirellus capitatus. A, C: male pygofer and segment X – XI, lateral and dorsal view, respectively; B: male pygofer side, lateral view; D: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E – F: style, dorsal view; G: connective, dorsal view; H: aedeagus, dorsal view; I: connective and aedeagus, lateral view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255857/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
A–B). Subgenital plate strongly convex laterally, macrosetae nearly uniseriate centrally (
<figureCitation box="[706,776,1873,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,207,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[206,1381,193,1472]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Stirellus capitatus. A, C: male pygofer and segment X – XI, lateral and dorsal view, respectively; B: male pygofer side, lateral view; D: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E – F: style, dorsal view; G: connective, dorsal view; H: aedeagus, dorsal view; I: connective and aedeagus, lateral view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255857/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
D). Style apophysis digitate, laterally curved (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1373,1873,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,207,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[206,1381,193,1472]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Stirellus capitatus. A, C: male pygofer and segment X – XI, lateral and dorsal view, respectively; B: male pygofer side, lateral view; D: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E – F: style, dorsal view; G: connective, dorsal view; H: aedeagus, dorsal view; I: connective and aedeagus, lateral view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255857/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
E–F). Connective stem shorter than arms (
<figureCitation box="[569,639,1909,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,207,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[206,1381,193,1472]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Stirellus capitatus. A, C: male pygofer and segment X – XI, lateral and dorsal view, respectively; B: male pygofer side, lateral view; D: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E – F: style, dorsal view; G: connective, dorsal view; H: aedeagus, dorsal view; I: connective and aedeagus, lateral view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255857/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
G). Aedeagal shaft long, strongly bent dorsally at near base and then sloping and bent ventrally, tip pointed and slightly curved dorsad (
<figureCitation box="[894,960,1945,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1493,1515]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,207,1455]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[206,1381,193,1472]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Stirellus capitatus. A, C: male pygofer and segment X – XI, lateral and dorsal view, respectively; B: male pygofer side, lateral view; D: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E – F: style, dorsal view; G: connective, dorsal view; H: aedeagus, dorsal view; I: connective and aedeagus, lateral view; J: aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255857/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
H–J).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1621,2006]" box="[199,871,1981,2006]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1981,2006]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Female.</emphasis>
Hind margin of seventh sternum straight (
<figureCitation box="[768,834,1981,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1981,2003]" captionTargetBox="[241,1342,471,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[229,1358,454,1959]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Stirellus capitatus. Female. A – D: habitus, dorsal view; E: habitus, lateral view; F: face; G: the end of female abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255856/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
G).
</paragraph>
